but can u watch it in windows media player
------------
VLC would be your best bet (in my own opinion, of course) if you are looking for a good media player.

In case anyone else had a problem with synch and couldn't get over the slight audio/video lag: open the movie with VLC Media Player, press CTRL-E, click the synchronization tab, in "advance of audio over video" set it to (-0.200s).

@ rimsmash at 2010-11-10 00:36 CET:
but can u watch it in windows media player

yes, provided you have the video codec. You can also download Media Player Classic. Also consider Klite codex for the ability to watch any format video.
